CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 13, 1956, pg. 1, reads: "West Donates Funeral - A Navy man stands guard as volunteer pallbearers carry last remains of Gold Star Mother. Left to right, Mr. Wilson, Thomas L. West and the Rev. James B. Cayce. - Harris Photo."  Her obituary reads: "Harris, Lenore of 97 Crawford St. (lately of 144 Elm St.) died in Mercy Hospital, Aug. 24.  Services here held Tuesday from West Funeral Home, with the Rev. James B. Cayce officiating.  There were no immediate survivors."
TitMainTitle: Men, including one wearing U.S. Navy sailor uniform, pallbearers, Mr. Wilson, Thomas L. West, and Rev. B. Cayce, standing outside of West's Funeral Home for funeral of Gold Star Mother Lenore Harris, 2216 Centre Avenue, Hill District
